    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe shiftwidth value returned from vim.api.* is wrong.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nThe current buffer's shiftwidth value is checked using:\r\n`lua print(vim.fn.shiftwidth())` returns 4 which is appropriately set for the text file.\r\n\r\nHowever, when I use:\r\n`local status_ok, buf_option = pcall(vim.api.nvim_buf_get_option, 0, \"shiftwidth\")` then buf_option prints value 8.\r\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe buf_option should return 4. Even if pass the current buffer using `vim.api.nvim_get_current_buf`, it always returns 8.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.9.4\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nshiftwidth() when used from .vim file worked correctly\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nUbuntu 22.04 LTS\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\ngnome-terminal\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\ndeb",
