            "body": "> `echo nvim_get_option_value('sw', { 'buf': 0})`\r\n\r\nThe value return is 4.\r\n\r\n> What sets 'shiftwidth' to 4?\r\n\r\nIt's initially set to 2. There is a plugin called guess-indent that changes it to 4.\r\n\r\n```\r\n      vim.g.neoformat_c_clangformat = {\r\n        exe = \"clang-format\",\r\n        args = {\r\n          '--style=\"{BasedOnStyle: Google, ColumnLimit: 120, IndentWidth: '\r\n            .. tostring(get_buf_option(\"shiftwidth\"))\r\n            .. '}\"',\r\n        },\r\n      }\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is how I'm trying to set it. I just checked, even in vimscript, I'm facing this issue. If I try to concat a value inside that json string, it will give 8 instead of 4. However, if I just keep it 4 (static), this doesn't happen.\r\n\r\nInteresting issue.",
